# Situation

You are running inside ~/dataroom, a daily activity collection system. You sit on top of personal data from 16 channels and can run scripts to refresh any of them.

## Reading collected data

Each channel stores its latest output in `collect/{channel}/data/latest.txt`:

| Channel | What's in it |
|---------|-------------|
| md | Recently modified markdown files (30 days) |
| tex | Recently modified LaTeX files (3 years) |
| mail | Sent emails from Mail.app — iCloud + ENS (7 days) |
| mail_flagged | Flagged emails from Mail.app (7 days) |
| tweets | Saved tweet activity + catalogue (7 days) |
| telegram | Recent Telegram conversations (7 days) |
| pdf | Downloaded PDFs/presentations (30 days) |
| notes | Apple Notes (30 days) |
| arxiv | ArXiv papers visited in Safari/Chrome (30 days) |
| chatgpt | ChatGPT conversation export (30 days) |
| claude | Claude conversation export (30 days) |
| deepseek | DeepSeek conversation export (30 days) |
| calendar | Google Calendar events (±7 days) |
| vscode | VS Code workspace activity (30 days) |
| youtube | Watch Later playlist changes (snapshot diff) |
| safari_bookmarks | New Safari bookmarks (30 days) |

## Richer data

- **Tweets**: `collect/tweets/data/catalogue` has the full tweet index. Saved tweets live in `collect/tweets/data/saved/{username}/{id}/tweet.md` (full text + images).
- **Tweet bookmarks**: `collect/tweets/data/bookmarks.json`
- **Telegram**: `collect/telegram/data/latest.json` (structured message data)
- **Safari bookmarks**: `collect/safari_bookmarks/data/state.json` (full bookmark tree with page summaries)
- **Summaries**: `summaries/summary_YYYY-MM-DD.md` — daily digests combining all channels

## Running collectors

Refresh a single channel:
  uv run collect/{channel}/scripts/{script_name}.py

Key scripts:
- `collect/tweets/scripts/fetch_bookmarks.py` — fetch latest tweet bookmarks
- `collect/tweets/scripts/fetch_tweet.py <url>` — save a specific tweet
- `collect/telegram/scripts/fetch_activity.py` — refresh Telegram data
- `collect/safari_bookmarks/scripts/fetch_bookmarks.py` — refresh bookmarks
- `collect/calendar/scripts/fetch_events.py` — refresh calendar

Full collection + summary pipeline:
  uv run collect.py

## Notes

- All scripts use `uv run`, not pip or python directly
- Working directory is the repo root (~/dataroom)
- Credential files in `config/` dirs are gitignored — never print their contents
- Browser history queries need Full Disk Access (may fail in some terminals)


